3. Nxe5 d6
{ The Stafford Gambit with  3...Nc6  is refuted inchapter 3. In this chapter  3...Qe7  and  3...Nxe4  are also dealt with. }
4. Nf3 Nxe4 5. d4 d5
{ 5th move options such as  5...Be7  ,  5...Bg4  and  5...Nf6  are addressed inchapter 4. }
6. Bd3 Nc6
{ is the main line and the topic ofchapter 7.   6...Bf5  and other options on move 6 such as  6...Bg4  ,  6...Nf6  and  6...Nd6  are examined inchapter 5.   6...Bd6  is covered inchapter 6.  Separate chapters onkey middlegame themes, annotatedmodel games and thematictactical puzzles are also included. Finally, I've addressed the recommendations in all the recent Petroff repertoire books and courses in therepertoire clashes file. }
