Bg4
{ Black has just played ...Bg4, 'threatening' to win the d4 pawn with ...Nxd4. In the game Kasparov,G @@StartBracket@@2740@@EndBracket@@-Karpov,A @@StartBracket@@2705@@EndBracket@@ 1986, Kasparov correctly ignored Black's 'threat' and instead struck in the center with }
8. c4 { The d4 pawn is untouchable as } 8... Nxd4
{ loses material to   Karpov correctly opted for  8...Nf6  which was one of the main theoretical battlegrounds in the 90s. }
9. Bxe4 dxe4 { 9...Bxf3  10.Bxf3  Nxf3+  11.Qxf3+- } 10. Qxd4 Bxf3 11. Qe5+ Qe7
12. Qxe7+ Bxe7 13. gxf3 { White is a piece up. } *

