15. Re3
{ is another common way of doubling on the e-file. Not only is Rae1 coming, but White's rook can also swing over to g3/h3 to attack Black's king. }
15... Bf6 16. Rae1 Re7 17. Bg5 Rxe3 18. fxe3
{ is an unusual but very interesting recapture. Rather than the natural Rxe3, White chooses to open the f-file to attack Black's king. Furthermore, White has ambitions of expanding in the center with e4. }
18... Bxg5 19. Nxg5 g6 20. e4 Re8 21. Qg3
{ White had a big advantage, going on to win in 1-0 @@StartBracket@@66@@EndBracket@@ Yagupov,I @@StartBracket@@2442@@EndBracket@@-Sorokin,M @@StartBracket@@2554@@EndBracket@@ St Petersburg 2001. }
