{ In the game 1-0  (63)  Timman,J  (2610)  -Van der Wiel, J  (2515)  Tilburg 1984, Black countered }
6. Bd3 { with } 6... f5
{ maintaining the knight on e4. This, however, drastically weakens the e6 square, which Timman immediately exploited with }
7. c3 Nd7 8. Qb3
{ This queen sortie is particularly strong here due to the threats of Qxb7 and Qe6+.   In general, the maneuver Qd1-b3, breaking the pin with tempo, crops up in several variations of the Petroff. Even if Black can cripple our pawn structure with ...Bg4xf3, the queen's position is sometimes so powerful that this is of little consequence. }
