{ In the game Kotronias,V  (2590)  -Skembris,S  (2525)  Corfu 1995, Kotronias probed Black's kingside with the following bishop and queen battery }
11. Qc2 g6
{ is a mistake.   Alternatively  11...Nf6?  is strongly met by  12.Ng5  with a double-attack on the bishop on e6 and the h7 pawn.  12...Nde4  13.Nxe6  fxe6  14.f3  winning material. For example  14...Bd6  15.Bxd6  Nxd6  16.Rxe6±  leaves White with an extra pawn.   11...h6!  is the correct reaction, which was played in the aforementioned game. }
12. Bh6 Re8
{ 12...Nf6  is necessary but after  13.Bxf8  Bxf8  14.Nbd2+-  White is an exchange up. }
13. Rxe6 { Boom! } 13... fxe6 14. Bxg6
{ crashes through. Black's king is toast. } 14... hxg6
{ 14...Nf8  doesn't help as White can continue with  15.Bxh7+!  Nxh7  16.Qg6+  Kh8  17.Qg7 }
