{ The c3 + d4 pawn center vs Black's c7 pawn is a typical structure in the Petroff, which usually arises when Black plays ...Ne4xc3.   The following position occurred in several games, an example being ½-½  (30)  Kasparov,G  (2851)  -Anand,V  (2769)  Linares 2000. In this structure, an important theme is to expand with }
16. c4 Qd8 { followed by } 17. d5 Nb8 18. Qc2
{ gaining a lot of space and pushing back Black's pieces. This advance is particularly powerful when Black has fianchettoed his light-squared bishop, which is now out of the game. Furthermore, White now has good attacking chances with the Qc2 + Bd3 battery as well as Bb2 to target the g7 pawn. }
