1. h3
{ is a very creative idea by Kramnik, which featured in the high level game ½-½ @@StartBracket@@51@@EndBracket@@ Kramnik,V @@StartBracket@@2807@@EndBracket@@-Anand,V  @@StartBracket@@2753@@EndBracket@@ Wijk aan Zee 2003. White's idea is to transfer the knight to e3 with Nh2-g4-e3. }
1... Bf6 2. Nh2
{ Compared to the alternative route Nd2-f1-e3, this maneuver gains a tempo on the bishop on f6. It also gives White the extra option of Ng4-e5. }
2... Qa5 3. Bd2 Rcd8 4. Bf3 h6 5. Ng4 Bxg4 6. hxg4
{ The two bishops and superior central control gave White a slight advantage.   The alternative recapture  6.Bxg4  is not as strong as after  6...Rxe1  7.Qxe1  Black can now play  7...Ne7=  This move would not have been possible if White's bishop were on f3 exerting pressure on Black's queenside. The second player is now ready to break with ...c5 and enjoys easy equality. }
