{ This symmetrical pawn structure is typical of the mainline of the Petroff. While the center is locked and Black is quite solid, White can start active operations on the queenside and/or the kingside.   In the game 1-0  (59)  Anton Guijarro,D  (2694)  -Smeets,J  (2585)  Wijk aan Zee 2020, White first provoked a weakening of Black's queenside with }
13. Qc2 { hitting the h7 pawn. } 13... g6 14. Ne3 Rfe8 15. h4
{ started a big attack. Due to the weaknesses created by ... g6, this attack gains in strength and makes the kingside the ideal theater of operations. }
15... Bf8 16. Ng5 Nd8 17. h5
{ White's attack was well underway and he went on to win. } *

