1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nxe5 d6 4. Nf3 Nxe4
{ Black may look to be ahead in development, having already moved his d-pawn and centralized his knight. However, appearances are deceptive as the knight on e4 is a target, which will allow us to develop with tempi. }
5. d4 Nf6
{ This early retreat can transpose to one of the mainlines if Black plays ...d5 in short order. In this chapter, we'll be covering Black's alternative setups. }
6. Bd3 Be7
{ 6...d5  transposes to one of the mainlines at Black's disposal. Seechapter 5 for the details. }
7. h3
{ Stops any ...Bg4 shenanigans. Black's light-squared bishop is now restricted given we control the g4 and f5 squares. }
7... O-O 8. O-O d5
{ is almost a position from the Exchange French. Before you fall asleep or write hello@chessable.com a long worded email condoning transpositions to the boring Exchange French, notice that we've got the valuable h2-h3 move in for free. This guarantees White an advantage!   Alternatively  8...c5  fails to adequately challenge White's center. After  9.c4  d5  10.cxd5  cxd4  11.Nxd4  Qxd5  12.Nc3±  The knight on d4 is untouchable and the advantage in activity gave White a big advantage in 1-0 @@StartBracket@@44@@EndBracket@@ Manakova,M @@StartBracket@@2331@@EndBracket@@-Rakic,M  @@StartBracket@@2218@@EndBracket@@ Kac 2008. }
9. Re1 Nc6
{ An alternative piece arrangement based on  9...Nbd7  , intending to transfer the knight to f8, is a bit too slow. White can continue with  10.Bf4  Re8  11.Nbd2  Nf8  12.c3⩲  with ideas of Ne5 followed by N2f3 gives White a stable advantage. }
10. a3 { is an important move, preventing ...Nb4 followed by ...Bf5. } 10... h6
11. Nc3 Re8 12. Bf4
{ Both of our bishops are more active than Black's ones. Black's light-squared bishop, in particular, has no good places to go as we have full control over the f5 and g4 squares.  White was already much better, going on to win in 1-0 @@StartBracket@@29@@EndBracket@@ Burg,T @@StartBracket@@2589@@EndBracket@@-Bendana Guerrero,G @@StartBracket@@2441@@EndBracket@@ ICCF email 2014. }
