1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nxe5 d6 4. Nf3 Nxe4 5. d4 d5 6. Bd3
{ In this chapter, we cover all of Black's options on move 6 apart from the two mainlines with  6...Bd6  and  6...Nc6  . }
6... Bf5
{ occurred in 600+ OTB games. This is a frequent choice of top Chinese GMs and Polish superstar Jan-Krzysztof Duda.   Setups with  6...Be7  where Black does not go for a setup based on ...Nc6 are covered in this chapter. Setups involving ...Nc6 are discussed inchapter 7.   6...Bg4  was essayed in 700+ OTB games.   6...Nf6  has been played in 300+ OTB games.   6...Nd6  is pretty rare with only 150+ OTB games. }
