15. c4 { undermining Black's d-pawn. } 15... dxc4 16. Nxc4 Nb5
{ ..but we can ignore it and instead centralize our knight with } 17. Nce5
{ which discourages ...Nxd4 by virtue of the pressure on the f7 pawn and attacks Black's knight on b5. }
17... Nbc7
{ Look at Black's pieces! They are all on the first three ranks.   17...Nbxd4  runs into  18.Nxd4  Qxd4  19.Bc4±  with a great deal of pressure on the f7 pawn. Rad1 and Qf3 are on the agenda. }
18. Bc4
{ gave White a big edge in the game 1-0 @@StartBracket@@47@@EndBracket@@ Lei, T @@StartBracket@@2537@@EndBracket@@-Zhai,M @@StartBracket@@2310@@EndBracket@@ China 2018. The immediate threat is Nxf7 while Rad1 and/or Ng4 followed by Be5 are also in the cards. }
