Nxh7+
{ Picks up Black's rook with check. And no, we're not running out of gas! }
21... Kg7 22. Nxf8 Kxf8 23. Bh6+ Ng7 24. Re5
{ followed by Rae1 is decisive.  White has two pawns, a knight and a rook for the queen. Material is approximately level but Black is busted. He's completely pinned down and will have to give up even more material to avoid getting mated.   For example  24...Re8  25.Rae1  f6  26.Ng6+  Kf7  27.Rxe8  Nxe8  28.h5  Cages in Black's king. The idea is Bf8 followed by Re7+!  28...Qd8  29.Bf8  Ng7  30.h6  Kxg6  31.hxg7  Kf7  32.Re3+-  and Black can't do a single thing about Rh3 followed by Rh8. What a remarkable tactical sequence! }
