19. Qg3
{ @@StartBlockQuote@@Timing is everything! - Bobby Fisher @@EndBlockQuote@@The queen swings over to the kingside just in time to cover the c7 bishop, which forces Black to play }
19... fxg5 20. hxg5 Rf7 21. Nf3
{ not only gives White more than enough compensation for the exchange but also good practical chances of scoring a full point. Black's king is very exposed, the dark-squares being particularly vulnerable.  Coming up is Bf4 with the idea Ne5 when Black has to be very precise to not get mated.   Accurate play by both sides continues  21...Raf8  22.Bf4  Bd6  is necessary. Black cannot allow White's knight to land on e5.  23.Be5  f4  24.Qh2  Re7  25.Bf6  Re2  26.Qh6  Threatens to end the game with g6 right away. This forces  26...Qf7  27.Qh3  Qe6  28.Qh6  Qf7  with a repetition. If Black finds all of this, then he has surely earned a draw! @@StartBracket@@White can also continue with 29. Re1 by the way@@EndBracket@@. }
*

[Event "?"]
