[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "6. Petroff | 5...d5 6...Bd6"]
[Black "8...Nf6"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nxe5 d6 4. Nf3 Nxe4
{ Black may look to be ahead in development, having already moved his d-pawn and centralized his knight. However, appearances are deceptive as the knight on e4 is a target, which will allow us to develop with tempi. }
5. d4 d5
{ is by far Black's most common move. The second player takes a stake in the center and establishes his knight on e4. }
6. Bd3
{ If Black's knight were on f6 instead of e4, this would be a position from the Exchange French. While this may seem like an improved version for Black, the knight on e4 is a target. We'll be undermining it with moves like Re1, c4, Qc2 and/or Nbd2/Nc3 depending on Black's setup. }
6... Bd6
{ In this setup, Black abstains from exerting pressure against White's center with 6...Nc6. Instead, he prefers to reinforce the d5-pawn with ...c6 in the near future. }
7. O-O O-O
{ is the only sensible move.   7...Bg4?!  runs into  8.c4  undermining Black's knight and d5 pawn. Following  8...O-O  9.cxd5  Nf6  10.Nc3⩲  consolidates White's extra pawn. }
8. c4
{ is almost invariably played. The only way to put pressure on Black's position is to undermine the e4 knight and d5 pawn. This move is especially effective when Black develops his bishop to d6 as his control over the d5 pawn is reduced.  Retreating with   8.Nbd2  fails to put enough pressure on Black's e4 knight, which can be easily reinforced with ...Bf5 and ...Re8. For example  8...Bf5  9.Re1  Re8  10.Nf1  Bg6  11.Ne3  c6  12.c4  Nf6  13.Bxg6  hxg6  14.Qb3  Qb6=  Black fully equalized in the top level game 1/2-1/2 @@StartBracket@@48@@EndBracket@@ Anand,V @@StartBracket@@2768@@EndBracket@@ -Caruana,F @@StartBracket@@2822@@EndBracket@@ Saint Louis 2018. }
8... Nf6 { makes little sense as it allows White to push ahead with } 9. c5
{ gaining space with tempo. } 9... Be7 10. Be3 b6 11. a3 bxc5 12. dxc5
{ followed by Nd2 and Re1 give White a clear edge. The d4 square will be a natural outpost for the f3 knight later on. }
