11... Bh5
{ is the only good reply.   Taking a knight is a mistake  11...Bxf3?!  12.Qxf3  In the game 1-0 Zilka, Stepan @@StartBracket@@2530@@EndBracket@@ vs Penz, Harald @@StartBracket@@2308@@EndBracket@@ 2018. Black tried  12...Bd6  and quickly got into trouble after  13.Rae1  Ne7  14.Re2  Qd7  15.Rfe1  c6  16.Qh5  g6  17.Qh4  f6  18.Re6+-   Retreating with  11...Be6  is also no good. Following  12.Re1  a6  13.Re2  Qd7  14.Bf4  Bd6  15.Bxd6  Qxd6  16.Ng5  g6  White now has  17.Rxe6!  fxe6  followed by  18.Nxh7!  crashing through.  18...Rf7  19.Ng5  Rf6  20.Qg4  Kg7  21.f4  Raf8  22.g3+-  with full control and a decisive advantage. }
