{ is somewhere between equal and a slight advantage depending on the engine you ask. The main point is White's position is far easier to play. A testament to this is the game 1-0 @@StartBracket@@108@@EndBracket@@ Gumularz,S @@StartBracket@@2483@@EndBracket@@ -Socko,B @@StartBracket@@2627@@EndBracket@@ Warsaw 2019, where White caused a big upset.   White can look to target Black's queenside pawns with Qb5 and/or undermine Black's d5 pawn with b3 followed by c4. Starting active play on the kingside with Rh1 and h4 is also worth considering. }
